Clair V3 Audit Summary (Intake → Affect → Memory → Verification → Runtime)
Intake Layer
Clean input collection and normalization.

Major fix: removed early reasoning from processor.py.

Document reader split: ingestion stays, retrieval/memory formatting moved downstream.

Seeds and scenarios moved out of intake.

Decision Layer
Validator reclassified as Action Selection.

Reasoning module split into: reasoning core, retrieval, hazard detection, calibration, response formatting.

Planning Layer
Simulator kept for true planning only.

Retrieval, hazard detection, seed generation, and text helpers moved to proper layers.

Affect Layer
Risk assessor clean and stable.

Hypothalamus regulates global cognitive mode and behavioral hysteresis.

System‑Wide Pattern
V2 problem: modules became “too helpful” and blurred boundaries.

V3 fix: strict layer responsibilities enforced.

Memory Architecture
Working memory split into: core, promotion bridge, retrieval policy, truth governance, legacy compatibility.

Episodic memory clean and focused.

Long‑term memory modularized into storage, deduplication, conflict handling, normalization, scoring.

Routing
Thalamus router remains a pure dispatcher.

Central orchestrator extracted from overgrown V2 thalamus.

Verification
Source extraction, evidence evaluation, and verification orchestration reclassified under a dedicated verification subsystem.

Execution, Evaluation, Reflection
All three layers remain clean and isolated.

Reflection commits structured episodic records.

Evaluation provides deterministic scoring.

Execution simulates or performs actions with structured outputs.

Runtime (clair.py)
Over‑centralized in V2.

V3 splits into:

runtime/bootstrap

orchestrator

CLI interface

response manager

verification service wrapper

retrieval helpers

ingest helpers
